dren. Track visited nodes to avoid infinite recursion on circular deps (if already visited, return a leaf node with no children).\n- `detectCycles(name, registry)` - Find all circular dependency cycles. Return an array of cycles (each cycle is an array of plugin names forming the cycle), or null if no cycles exist.\n- `topologicalSort(name, registry)` - Return a topologically sorted list of all dependency names (dependencies first, the root plugin last). Throw/error if there are circular dependencies.\n- `flattenDependencies(name, registry)` - Return a flat list of all transitive dependency names (not including the root plugin itself). Each dependency should appear only once.\n- `hasCircularDependency(name, registry)` - Return true if any circular dependency exists in the tree\n- Export a `createDepsService()` function that creates and returns a `DepsService`\n- Import types with `import type { ... } from '../types.js';` (use .js extension for Node16 module resolution)\n- The module system is ESM\n- Do NOT import other modules from the project directly - the registry is passed as a parameter\n\nWrite the complete implementation file.\n"}]},"uuid":"010a6e48-c7e5-4c81-b69b-d6d60ee3f061","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:13:38.540Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Create the file `/workspace/src/deps/index.ts` implementing the `DepsService` interface from `/workspace/src/types.ts`.\n\nThe interface is:\n```typescript\nexport interface DepsService {\n  buildTree(name: string, registry: RegistryService): DependencyNode;\n  detectCycles(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[][] | null;\n  topologicalSort(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[];\n  flattenDependencies(name: string, registry: RegistryService): string[];\n  hasCircularDependency(name: string, registry: RegistryService): boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface DependencyNode {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: DependencyNode[];\n}\n\nexport interface RegistryService {\n  register(manifest: PluginManifest): void;\n  get(name: string): PluginManifest | null;\n  getVersion(name: string, version: string): PluginManifest | null;\n  list(): PluginManifest[];\n  search(query: string): PluginManifest[];\n  remove(name: string, version: string): boolean;\n  listVersions(name: string): string[];\n  update(name: string, version: string, updates: Partial<PluginManifest>): void;\n}\n\nexport interface PluginManifest {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  description: string;\n  author: string;\n  dependencies: Record<string, string>;\n  entryPoint: string;\n  permissions: string[];\n}\n```\n\nRequirements:\n- `buildTree(name, registry)` - Build a dependency tree starting from the named plugin. Use `registry.get(name)` to get the plugin manifest, then recursively build child nodes for each dependency. If a dependency is not found in the registry, create a leaf node with version \"unknown\" and no children. Track visited nodes to avoid infinite recursion on circular deps (if already visited, return a leaf node with no children).\n- `detectCycles(name, registry)` - Find all circular dependency cycles. Return an array of cycles (each cycle is an array of plugin names forming the cycle), or null if no cycles exist.\n- `topologicalSort(name, registry)` - Return a topologically sorted list of all dependency names (dependencies first, the root plugin last). Throw/error if there are circular dependencies.\n- `flattenDependencies(name, registry)` - Return a flat list of all transitive dependency names (not including the root plugin itself). Each dependency should appear only once.\n- `hasCircularDependency(name, registry)` - Return true if any circular dependency exists in the tree\n- Export a `createDepsService()` function that creates and returns a `DepsService`\n- Import types with `import type { ... } from '../types.js';` (use .js extension for Node16 module resolution)\n- The module system is ESM\n- Do NOT import other modules from